                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1227">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1227">Sleepers of
          Ephesus</persName> were the
          protagonists of a legend set in the time of the emperor <persName>Decius</persName>. Seven or eight children
            of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/623">Ephesus</placeName> were entombed in a cave
                        with their dog <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3018">Qitmir</persName> until they awoke 190 years later. The legend dates to the middle of the fifth
          century.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1227-1">
                        <desc>These saints are venerated on Oct. 22 (BHO).</desc>
                    </event>
